            "answer_text": "In a test, you either pass or fail; 2 possible situations. If 72% of the total students passed. That means 28% of the students failed. You now have all the ingredients in order to solve this problem. Now set up a proportion, 28/100=392/x28/100=392/x where x represents the total number of students. Cross multiply and you know have, 392\u2217100=28\u2217x392\u2217100=28\u2217x Now divide 28 on both sides (392\u2217100)/28=x(392\u2217100)/28=x Do the arithmetic. The total number of students is 1400. ",
