            "answer_text": "If 72% of the total students passed the exams while 392 students failed, finding the total number of students that did the exams is done by finding the percentage of the students that failed the exams, which is done by taking 100% subtract 72% to find 28% as the number of students that failed the exams. The question that you should then ask yourself is that if 28% corresponds the 392 students who failed the exams, then what would 100% of the students correspond to? Take 100% and multiply it by 392 students then divide it by 28% to give you 1400. This now becomes the total number of students that sat for the examination. ",
